				 Polls not about riots alone: Cong
																								New Delhi, Dec. 3 (PTI): The Congress today attacked Gujarat chief minister Narendra Modi saying he should be tried and convicted for human rights violations, but refrained from focusing on the 2002 riots.																								Modis track record on the issue of human rights has been abysmal. Those who think that we are hesitant to rake it up, please note that we have been repeatedly raking up this issue, Congress spokesperson Abhishek Singhvi said.																								However, asked if the Congress would make the post-Godhra riots an issue in the elections, he said: We dont believe in a single issue. The Gujarat polls are not a one-issue election and not a one-person election. It is an assessment of the BJP on all fronts, on all issues, on all facets.																								He said Modi should be tried and convicted by Indian courts as well as by the International Court of Justice.																								For a person of his track record, the phrase merchant of death is not only most appropriate but also mild, Singhvi said, referring to Sonia Gandhis speech last week in which she used the words.
